{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":254770,"duration_api_ms":230320,"num_turns":32,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"1fbdd598-b390-4d81-98bb-2f0ace229325","total_cost_usd":1.5841772500000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":22,"cache_creation_input_tokens":100549,"cache_read_input_tokens":1402822,"output_tokens":10169,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":100549,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":22,"outputTokens":10169,"cacheReadInputTokens":1402822,"cacheCreationInputTokens":100549,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":1.5841772500000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"TaskRunEntry.milestone_id is marked Option<String> with #[serde(default, skip_serializing_if = \"Option::is_none\")] (model.rs:277-278), but the acceptance criteria states: \"New fields (run_id, plan_hash, outcome_detail, milestone_id) should be required (non-optional) where they are known at write time.\" milestone_id is always known at write time — it's passed as a parameter to every write path. Make milestone_id a required String field. This also removes the need for backfill-on-read in FsTaskRunLineageStore::read_task_runs_from_path (fs.rs:2556-2558) and the canonicalize_entry_for_write method that patches it up.","rationale":"The acceptance criteria explicitly requires milestone_id to be non-optional since there is no existing data on disk requiring backward compatibility. Keeping it optional with backfill-on-read is exactly the kind of 'legacy parsing, backfill-on-read, or repair path' the spec says to remove. A required field enforces correctness at the type level rather than relying on runtime patching."},{"body":"Remove CompletionJournalDetails::parse_legacy (fs.rs:2289-2321) and the legacy-format branch in repairable_completion_event (fs.rs:2449-2459) that handles comma-delimited 'project=..., outcome=...' journal details. The acceptance criteria states: 'Remove any legacy parsing, backfill-on-read, or repair paths that only exist to handle a hypothetical migration from an older schema.' Since there is no existing milestone data on disk, the only journal details format is the structured JSON written by render_completion_journal_details. The parse_legacy path adds dead code and masks serialization bugs.","rationale":"This code handles a comma-delimited format that was never written to disk by the current implementation. Its existence contradicts the acceptance criteria's explicit instruction to remove legacy migration paths. parse_legacy also cannot correctly handle fields containing commas, creating a latent correctness risk if it were ever triggered."},{"body":"Remove the backward-compat deserialization test task_run_entry_backward_compat_without_new_fields (service.rs:1232-1245) and the legacy-backfill test read_task_runs_backfills_milestone_id_for_legacy_entries (service.rs:1247-1282). These tests validate migration behavior from an older schema that the acceptance criteria says does not exist. Also remove progress_deserialization_defaults_skipped_beads (model.rs test) if skipped_beads is made a required field (removing its #[serde(default)] annotation at model.rs:204).","rationale":"The acceptance criteria says 'No backward compatibility with old NDJSON schemas is required — there is no existing milestone data on disk.' Tests that validate deserialization of old-format JSON without the new fields exist purely to cover a hypothetical migration that should not be supported. Keeping them signals to future developers that backward compat is a design goal when it isn't."},{"body":"Remove the unused _started_at parameter from find_matching_running_task_run (model.rs:421). The parameter is prefixed with _ to suppress the dead-code warning but is never referenced in the function body. Update the single call site in FsTaskRunLineageStore::record_task_run_start (fs.rs:2815-2821) to stop passing it.","rationale":"Dead parameters add cognitive overhead and make the API harder to reason about. Since this function is a public model-layer query, the unused parameter misleads callers into thinking started_at plays a role in matching logic when it does not."}],"summary":"Reviewed all changed files (model.rs, service.rs, fs.rs, Cargo.toml) end-to-end. All 667 tests pass, clippy is clean, and the core architecture — ports, service use-cases, FS adapter with advisory file locking, and the collapse/merge logic for append-only NDJSON — is well-structured and correct. The main issues found are violations of the acceptance criteria's explicit instruction to make new fields required (not optional) and to remove legacy migration/backfill code, since no existing milestone data exists on disk. Four amendments proposed: (1) make milestone_id a required String field, (2) remove the legacy comma-delimited journal details parser, (3) remove backward-compat tests for old schema formats, (4) remove the unused _started_at parameter from find_matching_running_task_run. No runtime bugs or safety issues were found."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"55fe6c89-cb48-430b-8575-2bb6cd4e7c18"}
